# MotionEye Patterns

## APIs

| API | Port | Purpose |
|-----|------|---------|
| MotionEye Config | 8765 | `GET /config/list`, `POST /config/{id}/set/` with signature auth |
| Motion HTTP | 7999 | `/{id}/action/snapshot`, optional `detection/status` |
| MJPEG Stream | 9080+id | Live image (no login when auth disabled) |

## Signature auth (MotionEye 0.43.x)

- `_username` + `_signature` query parameters
- Sign key = SHA1(plain password) hex, or empty string when no password
- Implementation in `lib/motionEyeApi.js` — do not duplicate signature auth logic

```javascript
const { createMotionEyeApi } = require('./lib/motionEyeApi');

const api = createMotionEyeApi({
  host: config.motionHost,
  motionEyePort: config.motionEyePort,
  username: config.motionEyeUser,
  password: config.motionEyePassword,
  requestTimeoutMs: config.requestTimeoutMs,
});
```

## Mode profiles

- `off` — no detection, no webhook
- `still` — motion trigger, no video
- `sharp` — motion + MP4 recording; use `movie_format: 'mp4'` **without OMX**

## Stream HTML

- Poll MJPEG port before setting `streamUrl`
- `streamPausedHtml` = empty when stream off
- `publishSiblingStreamRelink()` after VIS re-render (multi-camera dashboards)
- Delays from `native` config — never hardcode

## Webhook (Phase 1+)

```
MotionEye → http://<ioBroker-IP>:<webhookPort>/motioneye.0/webhook/<cameraId>?value=true
```

- `cameraId` = internal key from `native.cameras[]`, not MotionEye numeric ID
- Auto-reset `.motion` after `motionResetMs`

## Channel names

- User-chosen display name → channel via `safe(name)` (spaces → `_`, sanitize special chars)
- Decouple ioBroker name from MotionEye camera name

## Known pitfalls

- Motion restart after `config/set` — 5–15 s offline; delay stream HTML
- VIS re-render can briefly black out other streams — sibling relink
- Passwords only in adapter instance `native`, never in repo
